A similar workflow was applied to ACE2-bound S variants. For S-Beta: ACE2, a 3.2 Å cryo-EM map of S-Beta engaged with ACE2 in a 3:3 stoichiometry (3 ACE2-bound) was obtained (Extended Data Fig. 8). For S-Gamma, S-Delta and S-Kappa:ACE2, a 2 ACE2-bound population was separated from the dominant 3 ACE2-bound population to generate separate sets of cryo-EM maps (Extended Data Figs. 9-11
). To improve the resolution of the binding interface between RBD and ACE2 for all S variants, another round of local refinement with a focused mask covering the interface was performed. The focus masks were created by UCSF-ChimeraX43. This yielded a separate set of cryo-EM maps of focus-refined ACE2 in complex with RBD with nominal resolutions ranged between 3.0 and 3.0 Å (Extended Data Figs. 8-11
).
